alerts.title: Special Weather Statement for Montgomery, PA
alerts.description:
...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL AFFECT NORTHEASTERN CHESTER...
SOUTHEASTERN BERKS AND WESTERN MONTGOMERY COUNTIES...
AT 910 PM EDT...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WAS NEAR FLYING HILLS...MOVING
EAST AT 30 MPH.
WIND GUSTS TO 40 MPH ARE POSSIBLE WITH THIS STORM.
FREQUENT CLOUD TO GROUND LIGHTNING IS OCCURRING. DO NOT STAY IN THE
OPEN NOR SEEK SHELTER UNDER TREES WHEN LIGHTNING THREATENS...MOVE
INDOORS WHEN A THUNDERSTORM APPROACHES.
VERY HEAVY RAIN WILL CAUSE WATER TO POND ON ROADS AND FILL POOR
DRAINAGE AREAS. THE RAIN CAN CAUSE RAPID RISES ON SMALL STREAMS AND
CREEKS.
THIS STORM WILL BE NEAR BIRDSBORO AROUND 920 PM...CEDARVILLE AROUND
930 PM...CEDARVILLE AROUND 940 PM...ROYERSFORD AROUND 950 PM AND
TRAPPE AROUND 1000 PM.

alerts.title: Flood Advisory for Montgomery, PA
alerts.description:
THE NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE IN MOUNT HOLLY NJ HAS ISSUED AN
* URBAN AND SMALL STREAM FLOOD ADVISORY FOR...
WARREN COUNTY IN NORTHWEST NEW JERSEY...
HUNTERDON COUNTY IN NORTHWEST NEW JERSEY...
MORRIS COUNTY IN NORTHERN NEW JERSEY...
NORTHERN SOMERSET COUNTY IN NORTHERN NEW JERSEY...
SUSSEX COUNTY IN NORTHWEST NEW JERSEY...
EASTERN BERKS COUNTY IN EASTERN PENNSYLVANIA...
NORTHWESTERN BUCKS COUNTY IN SOUTHEAST PENNSYLVANIA...
LEHIGH COUNTY IN EASTERN PENNSYLVANIA...
NORTHWESTERN MONTGOMERY COUNTY IN SOUTHEAST PENNSYLVANIA...
NORTHAMPTON COUNTY IN EASTERN PENNSYLVANIA...
NORTH CENTRAL CHESTER COUNTY IN SOUTHEAST PENNSYLVANIA...
* UNTIL 1230 AM EDT
* AT 828 PM EDT A LINE OF SHOWERS AND THUNDERSTORMS WITH HEAVY
RAINFALL WAS MOVING INTO THE ADVISED AREA. THESE SHOWERS AND
STORMS ARE PRODUCING RAINFALL RATES OF ONE TO ONE AND A HALF
INCHES PER HOUR. THIS AMOUNT OF RAIN IN A ONE HOUR TIME FRAME
WILL LEAD TO POOR DRAINAGE FLOODING AND SOME RISES ON CREEKS
AND STREAMS.
* EXCESSIVE RUNOFF FROM HEAVY RAINFALL WILL CAUSE PONDING WATER IN
URBAN AREAS...HIGHWAYS...STREETS AND UNDERPASSES AS WELL AS OTHER
POOR DRAINAGE AREAS AND LOW LYING SPOTS.
